text.tspan: Rensselaer: Why are you interested in Rensselaer?
Brown: Why Brown, and why the Brown
Curriculum?
UW Honors College: The word “Honors” means
different things at different universities. Why do
you want to be a part of
Interdisciplinary Honors at the University of Washington?
UW Honors College: If you could pull
together any two living people and listen
to their conversation, who would they be
and why?
University of Washington: Tell a story from
your life, describing an experience that either
demonstrates your character or helped to shape
it.
Berkeley: What would you say is your
greatest talent or skill? How have you
developed and demonstrated that talent over time?
Berkeley: Describe an example of your leadership
experience in which you have positively influenced
others, helped resolve disputes, or contributed to
group efforts over time.
Georgia Tech: Beyond rankings, location, and athletics,
why are you interested in attending Georgia
Tech?
Georgia Tech: We challenge our students to
'be comfortable being uncomfortable'. Tell us about
a time in high school that you
felt outside of your comfort zone and
the resolution.
MIT: Tell us about something you do
for the pleasure of it.
MIT: Tell us about the most significant
challenge you've faced or something important that
didn't go according to plan. How did
you manage the situation?
Princeton: Your favorite movie:
Princeton: Your favorite website:
Princeton: Two adjectives your friends would use
to describe you:
Princeton: Your favorite recording:
Princeton: Your favorite keepsake or memento:
Princeton: Your favorite source of inspiration:
Princeton: Your favorite word:
Princeton: Your favorite line from a movie
or book and its title:
Stanford: Name one thing you are looking
forward to experiencing at Stanford.
Stanford: Imagine you had an extra hour
in the day — how would you
spend that time?
Stanford: Virtually all of Stanford's undergraduates live
on campus. Write a note to your
future roommate that reveals something about you
or that will help your roommate -
and us - know you better.
Stanford: What is the most significant challenge
that society faces today?
Stanford: What historical moment or event do
you wish you could have witnessed?
Stanford: What five words best describe you?
Stanford: When the choice is yours, what
do you read, listen to, or watch?
